I am now focusing on refining the reconnection strategy within the `LiveCall` component. My goal is to reliably handle "peer-id-taken" errors, which have been persistently blocking subsequent calls. I will implement a robust strategy that specifically addresses `peer.on('error')` errors to account for race conditions and server-side delays, with potential retries and new ID generation.


